Question: Explain to a child how to do a task (e.g., cross the street).
Answer:
Choose the street you desire to cross. Then make sure you have the right of way. In other words you are not interrupting traffic. Make sure to look both ways and then when the street is clear of passing cars you may cross the street. Make sure to cross on a cross walk so as not to J-walk. Try and walk at a swift pace as well. 